
	Insert the linux kernel headers using the command "sudo apt-get install linux-headers-$(uname -r)".
   
	Download the gyro.c ,script.py and Makefile

    Go to the directory in which code is downloaded and give the command $ make all

    Insert the module using sudo "insmod gyro.ko"

    Check if module is loaded using "lsmod" command

	Exit from current terminal and open a new terminal

	Check the kernel log using "dmesg -wH"
	
	Run the user space python script using the command "sudo python script.py"

    The angular acceleration rates in hex format is displayed as [X axis, Y axis, Z axis].

    Remove the module using sudo rmmod gyro.ko

